  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package intentionally references a published hemolysis modelling methodology paper (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) via referencesIdentifier to anchor the power-law hemolysis model selection rationale; however, no corresponding typed node for that IRI exists anywhere in this graph, triggering W-CON-02.",
